      "seed": 1365995391,
      "version": 37,
      "versionNonce": 252739413,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782143104036,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Problem Statement\nYou are tasked with designing the core call orchestration platform for a Fortune 500 financial services client. \nThe platform ingests campaign uploads (CSV files containing phone numbers and contact metadata) \nand is responsible for executing outbound voice AI calls against those contacts. \n\nCalls are placed through a third-party telephony provider (assume a generic SIP/voice API). \nEach call produces a transcript and a structured outcome (e.g., promise-to-pay, callback requested, voicemail), \nwhich must be delivered back to the client's CRM.\n\nYou should produce an initial system design diagram suitable for presenting to engineering stakeholders.\n\nYou will have 30 minutes for this challenge.\n\n\nFunctional Requirements\n\nAccept campaign uploads of up to 5 million contacts per file\nSchedule and dispatch outbound calls while respecting per-contact calling windows (no calls outside 8am-9pm local time)\nApply retry logic with backoff, up to 3 attempts per contact\nEnforce concurrency caps per campaign\nIntegrate with a third-party telephony provider to place calls\nCapture call outcomes and transcripts\nDeliver outcomes back to the client's CRM via webhook\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n\nSustain 1 million calls per day, with peak concurrency of 10,000 simultaneous calls\nCall dispatch must be scalable, with no single component bottlenecking throughput as campaigns grow\nOutcome delivery to CRM within 60 seconds of call completion\nAt-least-once delivery guarantees for outcomes\nFailure of any individual call execution must not affect other in-flight calls or block the campaign\nCloud provider: AWS preferred (assume generic cloud if unfamiliar)\nSystem should scale to support roughly 3x growth month-over-month",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Problem Statement\nYou are tasked with designing the core call orchestration platform for a Fortune 500 financial services client. \nThe platform ingests campaign uploads (CSV files containing phone numbers and contact metadata) \nand is responsible for executing outbound voice AI calls against those contacts. \n\nCalls are placed through a third-party telephony provider (assume a generic SIP/voice API). \nEach call produces a transcript and a structured outcome (e.g., promise-to-pay, callback requested, voicemail), \nwhich must be delivered back to the client's CRM.\n\nYou should produce an initial system design diagram suitable for presenting to engineering stakeholders.\n\nYou will have 30 minutes for this challenge.\n\n\nFunctional Requirements\n\nAccept campaign uploads of up to 5 million contacts per file\nSchedule and dispatch outbound calls while respecting per-contact calling windows (no calls outside 8am-9pm local time)\nApply retry logic with backoff, up to 3 attempts per contact\nEnforce concurrency caps per campaign\nIntegrate with a third-party telephony provider to place calls\nCapture call outcomes and transcripts\nDeliver outcomes back to the client's CRM via webhook\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n\nSustain 1 million calls per day, with peak concurrency of 10,000 simultaneous calls\nCall dispatch must be scalable, with no single component bottlenecking throughput as campaigns grow\nOutcome delivery to CRM within 60 seconds of call completion\nAt-least-once delivery guarantees for outcomes\nFailure of any individual call execution must not affect other in-flight calls or block the campaign\nCloud provider: AWS preferred (assume generic cloud if unfamiliar)\nSystem should scale to support roughly 3x growth month-over-month",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
